        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Acl currently utilizes a \"registry\" (class Zend_Acl_Aro_Registry) to store ARO objects in an organized manner. The underlying storage mechanism follows the Singleton pattern, and multiple instances of Zend_Acl appear to be forced to use the same ARO registry.\n\nIt may be desirable, however, that each instance of Zend_Acl would be able to encapsulate its own ARO registry. Though we do need to support the use case of multiple ACLs using the same ARO registry, it seems arbitrary and counterintuitive to impose that multiple ACL instances may exist and that they must share a single ARO registry. It is conceivable that completely unrelated ACL instances would not use the same ARO registry."
        },
